citeinfo.title: County Commissioner Districts, Ramsey County, Minnesota

descript.abstract: This dataset contains polygons that represent Ramsey County commissioner districts as of the redistricting process following the 2010 census.
descript.purpose: Commissioner districts are often used as boundaries for analyzing other GIS data, including census data, tax data, and county services.

theme.themekey: boundaries, commissioner districts, county commissioners, political boundaries

timeperd.current: Commissioner districts are modified following political re-districting activities. Attribution may also be changed following election of new commissioners.

horizpa.horizpar: Digitized information is generally +/- 7 feet; some areas have been found to be +/- 30 feet. COGO (coordinate geometry) accuracy generally is +/- 1.0 foot.

attracc.attraccr: Attributes are populated from a compilation of records and information from various state, county and city offices, and other sources. Accuracy may vary by source, but domains are used wherever possible to increase accuracy.

procstep.procdesc: The Ramsey County commissioner districts were created as part of a redistricting process following the 2010 census. The boundaries were created by merging Federal Census Blocks which had individually been assigned to a commissioner district.

dataqual.logic: Information is visually inspected and corrected as necessary.
